    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-02-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="504"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                <head>504. Telegram 1694 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d504fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/2–2856. Secret; Priority; Limit
                        Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1"
                        >Clough</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1956-02-28">February 28, 1956, 7:50 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d504-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d504-1"/>
                <p>1694. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>FYI Indian Embassy officer said February 28 that Embassy had sent copies Agreed
                    Announcement to some of individuals on lists given you by <persName
                        corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> and asked whether Department could provide
                    addresses of remainder. He was told we felt adequate publicity had already been
                    given Agreed Announcement and did not consider it necessary send copies to
                    individuals named in these lists. We had told <persName corresp="#p_WP_1"
                        >Wang</persName> in Geneva we did not intend investigate names he gave us
                    unless he showed these persons obstructed from leaving. He had made such
                    specific allegation in only one case which we had investigated but had been
                    unable locate individual and had asked <persName corresp="#p_WP_1"
                        >Wang</persName> for additional facts to enable us to investigate
                    further.</p>
                <p>In response inquiry regarding publicity given Agreed Announcement in prisons,
                    Embassy officer was told we had investigated and satisfied ourselves information
                    about Agreed Announcement was available to prisoners through newspaper and radio
                    facilities provided in prisons.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
